NY ❤️💛 thank u everyone who came out and made day 1 of our tour a special one. Who’s seeing us tonight for the after party 😈😎 @theapollo_id

It’s my birthday and we started it by performing my first headline ATL show 😭🙈 Thank you everyone who came to support and turnup for my birthday and first headline tour with my brother 4L @parlaypass 🔐 It’s been stressful and emotional time for me but all your energy gave me a diff kind of boost - I also blacked out off the casamigos my bad I went so crazy 😭🙏 anyway, thank you everyone who helped put this together and pulled up, y’all made this my best bday ever ❤️🫶💯 LA see y’all Saturday 12/10 😎

This week has been a blur and fr the most emotional week of my life. I’ve never laughed cried this much in a 7 day span lolz. I wanna thank everyone who came out in nyc, kc, atl. 5 shows in 4 days. And la next on Saturday..I didn’t wanna do this tour at first because I was scared I wouldn’t sell enough tix..I’ve felt like I never lived up to expectations and hated where I was in my music career. Wondering if I’m good enough to take my career to the next level and if I’m peaking and not meant to go further. This week of being on the road and not sleeping blacking out of Alcohal and other shit, I thought it was gonna break me. But seeing all your faces and all the good energy you gave me made me understand I’m on the right track, and surprised me tbh. I’ve been feeling lonely Af and broken and I realize I got so many people in my life that go so hard for me and It makes me wanna do the same. I love all of y’all and I never even thought I’d make it this far. I’m not the artist I wanna be yet, n more important I’m not the person I wanna be yet.. but we gonna grow together and share many more memories. I used to wanna kms and sometimes I still do. But I’m gonna keep fighting because when life gets ugly, there’s always something beautiful to fight for. Thank you everyone who’s come out to show me that we can really do this shit, and la we gonna finish strong and turn Tf up Saturday. I was scared these couple hundred cap rooms would be empty but y’all deff showed out for me instead 😭🙈 y’all bet on me and best believe, imma bet on myself and push this to the moon. Thank you all n much Love ❤️💯

LA 🥺❤️ Wouldn’t have wanted to end my first mini US headline tour any other way with my brother 4L @parlaypass 💯 Thank you all the fambase and special guests who came out to pack the @theechola , a night I’ll never forget 🫶💫 thank you @alexdayo_ @maxxlrose @livenation for taking a chance on me with this tour, @pluggedinsaho @goodjob1st  for an incredible 4 cities and all my special guests who popped out for LA 🥂 @justinparkofficial @akaviettrap @g2slife @junoflo @dbo0dbo @yelohill @yox_rick @yox_jaeyoung @samstanmusic @billyracxx @aydioslio @signedx0 @ayosk3tch @wakkothekidd @jamo.choi @liukhangg
LA ❤️💫 The finale to my first headline mini US tour with @parlaypass at @theechola was a movie, 🎥 by @sleepxtite 🤯🔥🔥 Thank you to the best fans & the best surprise guests 🫶💯

4 cities, 1 week. NYC, KC, ATL, LA. Exhausted and boutta sleep for a few days straight but wanted to thank everyone who came out and made some amazing memories with us on my first headline mini US tour with my mf twin 4L @parlaypass 

When @alexdayo_ brought up the possibility of me touring for the first time this summer, I didn’t know if I wanted to do it. Being the opener / support act knowing your going to perform for a filled up room with Jay, H1ghr, Dumb etc and being the main attraction who has to sell tix are two very diff situations and I deff didn’t believe I was ready to try n fill up a room..Dayo, Pass and @pluggedinsaho told me I was trippin and I decided to run it. And I’m forever grateful we did. 

To all the fans, friends, and artists who pulled up im forever grateful and will never forget the  craziest week of my life. I know these 250-350 cap rooms will become 500, then 1000 and who knows where it’ll go.. but as we grow together, I’m coming with a new confidence and new gratitude to where my passion has taken me. And I couldn’t have done it without all of you 🙏❤️💯 

Thank you everyone who took a chance on me with this. To many more 🫶🥂 Special thanks to @maxxlrose and @alexdayo_ for putting it all together 🔐

Pre save Butterfly on Spotify 🦋 link in bio

Since me & Pass linked up a lot of you guys have been asking for an album and we’re finally ready to share 💫 Our first single Butterfly is releasing 1/13/2023 off our back to back album series “The Pleasure” and “The Pain” coming out Spring 💔 Butterfly signifies the beginning of a new era, and also takes a moment to celebrate all our loved ones who passed away and spread their wings to whatever comes after this life 🦋

Presaving helps us a ton by strengthening our spotify presence and giving us a higher chance of playlisting so appreciate if everyone could take a second to do so. Excited to bring in 2023 with more music and to make more memories with y’all 🙏❤️

2022 was a crazy year with a lot of ups and downs.. but I’m thankful for every moment making me a stronger and happier person. Happy New Years thank you for every single on of you for making it special. To an even better 2023! 💫💛🍾 #reelsinstagram #explorepage #newyear #2022 #2023goals

Montreal - a lil serious post sorry 😭🙈
Before the show I was feeling tired and a lil disappointed in my performance n effort the night before. Just being hard on myself N exhausted overall. 

Y’all energy brought me up and made feel really special. Thank u for giving me 1000% and I tried my best to return it. 🖤🫡

Being on my bruddas tour has been really inspiring but i guess also got me thinking if I’ll ever get to that place where I’ll be able to do my own headline tour someday. The same doubt that has held me back from releasing full albums, from taking opportunities and made me wanna stop this too many times. 

This experience has opened my eyes and showed me that if I keep pushing n god willing I’ll get there some day. Appreciate everyone who’s been fw me in every city. Can’t believe we’re half way done, imma give y’all my best all the way till the end! Thank you again 4 last night, kespass MTL 🫶

Home Alone (audio) releasing tonight at 12AM est / 9PM pst on streaming platforms 🏠🫶 I’ve endlessly released music trying to see what sticks without really pushing it, and then just moved on to the next song. This is the first release where I don’t have my next song selected and I’m going to focus on getting this one out there because it’s really special to me 🙏❤️ We also shot my biggest MV to date which will come a few weeks later! 🎥 

Touring nonstop for 7 months was an amazing experience and I made the most amazing memories with y’all. At the same time, the non-stop drinking and partying really took a toll on me mentally and physically and I was going out of control and starting to get into a dark place mentally. I’ve struggled with finding what my purpose is and rather than facing a lot of my inner demons, I tried to numb it with other things. Recently, I’ve found myself really starting to be comfortable in my own skin and spending quality time alone finding peace rather than chasing a feeling every night. I’m so grateful for all my fanbase who have consistently rooted for and pushed me to be the best artist and person I can be and I’m so excited to give y’all the first song of my next chapter that really speaks on that. the music is gonna hit deeper and different and I couldn’t be more excited 😭💯 Home Alone boutta drop, stream this one like crazy for me, much love @we.are.snc @jrdynbeats  @fakedell and everyone involved ❤️🫶🤞

Home Alone is finally out now on streaming and I’ve never put out a song this personal to me in a long time. After touring for more than half my year and seeing such amazing places and people, the drinking partying and lack of sleep finally caught up to me 😭 I don’t think I’ve ever appreciated being home spending time to myself more than now and I can’t wait to come back recharged and the best version of myself 🫶🙏 keep streaming Home Alone and I’ll drop the MV 🎥
